    "Microfossils serve as vital tools in various fields.",
    "Their lower trophic level makes them abundant, and of great utility for stratigraphic correlation and for reconstructing past environments.",
    "In paleoclimatology, for example, the isotopic composition and morphological adaptations of microfossils can reveal past ocean temperatures, ice volumes, and other climatic conditions (Gersonde et al. 2005).",
    "This makes them indispensable for understanding climate patterns and environmental changes across geological eras (Sremac et al. 2024).",
